go_data.justification: DNAJC19 is part of the TIM23-PAM system, essential for the import of precursor proteins into the mitochondrial matrix.
DNAJC19 is described as a cochaperone associated with the TIM23-PAM system.
DNAJC19 is a mitochondrial cochaperone and interacts with the TIM23 complex, which is localized to the mitochondria.
DNAJC19 forms a complex with prohibitins to regulate cardiolipin remodeling.
